---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';

const siteUrl = 'https://www.lptaxiheraklion.com';
const slug = 'taxi-heraklion-to-chania';
const title = 'Taxi From Heraklion To Chania: Distance, Time And Tips';
const description = 'Everything you need to know about the 150 km drive from Heraklion to Chania by private taxi — distances, travel time, fares, and a stop in Rethymno.';
const image = '/images/DSC_8042.jpg';
const datePublished = '2026-04-28';

const jsonLd = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "BlogPosting",
  "headline": title,
  "description": description,
  "image": `${siteUrl}${image}`,
  "datePublished": datePublished,
  "dateModified": datePublished,
  "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "LP Taxi Heraklion", "url": siteUrl },
  "publisher": {
    "@type": "Organization",
    "name": "LP Taxi Heraklion",
    "logo": { "@type": "ImageObject", "url": `${siteUrl}/images/logo-lp.svg` }
  },
  "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": `${siteUrl}/blog/${slug}` }
};
---

<Layout title={`${title} | LP Taxi Heraklion`} description={description} ogImage={image} jsonLd={jsonLd}>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="relative pt-32 pb-16 bg-navy overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 opacity-10">
      <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 w-96 h-96 bg-gold rounded-full blur-3xl translate-x-1/2 -translate-y-1/2"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="relative max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <a href="/blog" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-gold hover:text-gold-light transition-colors text-sm font-semibold mb-6">
        <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M15 19l-7-7 7-7" />
        </svg>
        <span data-i18n="blog.backToBlog">Back to blog</span>
      </a>
      <span class="text-gold font-semibold text-sm tracking-widest uppercase">Routes</span>
      <h1 class="font-display text-3xl sm:text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-bold text-white mt-3 mb-6 leading-tight">{title}</h1>
      <p class="text-gray-400 text-lg leading-relaxed">{description}</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Featured image -->
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 -mt-8 mb-12">
    <div class="aspect-[16/9] rounded-2xl overflow-hidden shadow-xl">
      <img src={image} alt={title} class="w-full h-full object-cover" />
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Article body -->
  <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 pb-24">
    <div class="text-gray-700 text-lg leading-relaxed space-y-6">
      <p>The route from Heraklion to Chania is one of the most travelled in Crete. Whether you are switching accommodation, heading for a day trip, or connecting to the western part of the island, taking a private taxi is one of the best ways to cover this distance in comfort.</p>
      <p>Here is everything you need to know before you book.</p>

      <h2 class="font-display text-3xl font-bold text-navy mt-12 mb-4">How Far Is Heraklion From Chania?</h2>
      <p>The distance from <strong>Heraklion to Chania</strong> by road is approximately <strong>150 kilometers</strong>. The route follows the E75 motorway along the northern coast of Crete, passing through Rethymno along the way.</p>
      <p>This is a well-maintained highway with good visibility and consistent road quality throughout the year.</p>

      <h2 class="font-display text-3xl font-bold text-navy mt-12 mb-4">How Long Does The Drive Take?</h2>
      <p>Under normal conditions, the trip takes <strong>around 2 hours to 2 hours 30 minutes</strong>.</p>
      <p>Traffic, road works, or a stop along the way can add time. July and August bring more vehicles on the road, particularly around Heraklion, Rethymno, and the Chania approach. If you are in no rush, the scenery through the mountains and along the coastline makes the drive genuinely enjoyable.</p>

      <h2 class="font-display text-3xl font-bold text-navy mt-12 mb-4">How Much Does A Taxi From Heraklion To Chania Cost?</h2>
      <p>The fare for this long-distance route depends on the pickup and drop-off location, time of travel, vehicle type, and any stops along the way. For groups of 5 or more, a larger Mercedes vehicle is required, which carries a different rate.</p>
      <p>Rather than estimate a figure that may not match your exact journey, <a href="/booktaxionline" class="text-gold font-semibold hover:underline">get a confirmed fixed quote from LP Taxi Heraklion</a> before you travel. Knowing your total price in advance makes budgeting your trip much easier.</p>
      <p>Compared to renting a car (rental fee, fuel, insurance, parking in Chania), a private Mercedes taxi for 2 to 4 people is often surprisingly cost-effective, especially with no driving fatigue on a 150km route.</p>

      <h2 class="font-display text-3xl font-bold text-navy mt-12 mb-4">What About Stopping In Rethymno On The Way?</h2>
      <p>The road from Heraklion to Chania passes directly through Rethymno, making a stop there very easy to arrange. If you want to spend a few hours exploring Rethymno's old town and Venetian harbour before continuing to Chania, this is something you can discuss when booking.</p>
      <p>A stop in Rethymno is a popular choice. The town is beautiful, compact, and very walkable. Ask for a quote that includes the stop when you contact LP Taxi Heraklion.</p>

      <h2 class="font-display text-3xl font-bold text-navy mt-12 mb-4">Taxi vs. Bus For This Route</h2>
      <p>KTEL buses do operate between Heraklion and Chania, and they are reliable and affordable. The journey by bus takes approximately 3 hours or more, with set departure times from the Heraklion bus station.</p>
      <p>For travellers with luggage, families, or those who want door-to-door service, a private Mercedes taxi is significantly more convenient. You choose the departure time, you ride directly from your hotel or accommodation, and you arrive at your exact destination in Chania.</p>

      <div class="overflow-x-auto rounded-xl border border-gray-200 my-6">
        <table class="w-full text-left text-base">
          <thead class="bg-navy text-white">
            <tr>
              <th class="px-5 py-3 font-semibold"></th>
              <th class="px-5 py-3 font-semibold">Private Taxi</th>
              <th class="px-5 py-3 font-semibold">KTEL Bus</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-200">
            <tr><td class="px-5 py-3 font-medium">Door-to-door</td><td class="px-5 py-3">Yes</td><td class="px-5 py-3">No</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-cream"><td class="px-5 py-3 font-medium">Flexible departure</td><td class="px-5 py-3">Yes</td><td class="px-5 py-3">No</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="px-5 py-3 font-medium">Luggage space</td><td class="px-5 py-3">Comfortable</td><td class="px-5 py-3">Limited</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-cream"><td class="px-5 py-3 font-medium">Travel time</td><td class="px-5 py-3">2h to 2h30</td><td class="px-5 py-3">3h+</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="px-5 py-3 font-medium">Stops on request</td><td class="px-5 py-3">Yes</td><td class="px-5 py-3">No</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-cream"><td class="px-5 py-3 font-medium">Vehicle</td><td class="px-5 py-3">Mercedes</td><td class="px-5 py-3">Public bus</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <h2 class="font-display text-3xl font-bold text-navy mt-12 mb-4">Tips For Booking A Taxi From Heraklion To Chania</h2>
      <ol class="list-decimal pl-6 space-y-2">
        <li><strong>Book in advance, especially in summer.</strong> Long-distance taxis are in high demand during peak season.</li>
        <li><strong>Confirm the total price upfront.</strong> A reputable driver gives you a fixed quote before departure.</li>
        <li><strong>Specify pickup location clearly.</strong> Whether you are at a hotel, the port, or the airport, provide the exact address.</li>
        <li><strong>Ask about intermediate stops.</strong> If you want to stop at Rethymno or anywhere along the way, mention this when booking so it is included in your quote.</li>
      </ol>

      <h2 class="font-display text-3xl font-bold text-navy mt-12 mb-4">Book Your Taxi From Heraklion To Chania</h2>
      <p>LP Taxi Heraklion covers long-distance routes across Crete with professional drivers and modern Mercedes vehicles. Fixed pricing, comfortable ride, and direct service from your starting point to your destination.</p>
      <p><a href="/booktaxionline" class="text-gold font-semibold hover:underline">Book your Heraklion to Chania transfer online</a> and get your confirmed price before you travel. You can also call us directly at <a href="tel:+306943551122" class="text-gold font-semibold hover:underline">+30 694 355 1122</a>, available 24 hours a day.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Bottom CTA -->
    <div class="mt-16 p-8 sm:p-10 rounded-2xl bg-navy text-center">
      <h3 class="font-display text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-3" data-i18n="blog.cta.title">Ready to book your transfer?</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-300 mb-6" data-i18n="blog.cta.subtitle">Get a fixed price before you travel — no meter, no surprises.</p>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center">
        <a href="/booktaxionline" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2 bg-gold hover:bg-gold-light text-navy font-semibold px-8 py-4 rounded-xl transition-all text-lg shadow-lg shadow-gold/20" data-i18n="blog.cta.bookBtn">
          Book Your Ride
        </a>
        <a href="tel:+306943551122" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2 bg-white/10 hover:bg-white/20 text-white font-semibold px-8 py-4 rounded-xl transition-all text-lg border border-white/20">
          <svg class="w-5 h-5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M3 5a2 2 0 012-2h3.28a1 1 0 01.948.684l1.498 4.493a1 1 0 01-.502 1.21l-2.257 1.13a11.042 11.042 0 005.516 5.516l1.13-2.257a1 1 0 011.21-.502l4.493 1.498a1 1 0 01.684.949V19a2 2 0 01-2 2h-1C9.716 21 3 14.284 3 6V5z" />
          </svg>
          <span>+30 694 355 1122</span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>
